The paper discusses relevance judgment in information retrieval (IR) and user behavior in web search engines, which are both topics related to the sub-category of Information Retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also mentions the study of Order Effects in sequential decision making, which falls under the sub-category of Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of query logs, which is related to the sub-category of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) and Cybersecurity (cs.CY). Finally, the paper proposes a methodology for detecting irrational user behavior, which is related to the sub-category of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR).
